we saw an opportunity
to be generous.

00:14:29.120 --> 00:14:33.800
We'd happily give away
$100 in value every month

00:14:33.800 --> 00:14:37.260
if we knew you were going
to show up every day,

00:14:37.260 --> 00:14:41.610
month after month,
year after year.

00:14:41.610 --> 00:14:43.170
And it's working.

00:14:43.170 --> 00:14:46.750
Since we introduced
subscriptions last April,

00:14:46.750 --> 00:14:50.260
our subscription based has
grown month over month.

00:14:50.260 --> 00:14:53.610
So we're doing something right.

00:14:53.610 --> 00:14:56.100
Few top lines about
our subscriptions--

00:14:56.100 --> 00:14:59.370
in Legendary, we brand
our subscriptions as VIP.

00:14:59.370 --> 00:15:01.980
And during this talk,
I'm going to use

00:15:01.980 --> 00:15:05.400
those terms interchangeably,
subscriptions and VIP.

00:15:05.400 --> 00:15:07.840
It's $29.99 a month.

00:15:07.840 --> 00:15:12.540
Our VIP are a small but
growing portion of our revenue.

00:15:12.540 --> 00:15:15.240
We have 30,000
active subscribers.

00:15:15.240 --> 00:15:21.690
We have a day 425 retention
of 20% with our VIP actives.

00:15:21.690 --> 00:15:26.410
We have a 95% log
in rate of VIPs.

00:15:26.410 --> 00:15:29.370
And so far, cannibalization
is not a factor.

00:15:29.370 --> 00:15:32.185
And our cost per player
is coverable by our VIPs.

00:15:35.190 --> 00:15:39.540
Some key considerations
we thought about when

00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:42.360
introducing web subscriptions--

00:15:42.360 --> 00:15:46.290
we thought of subscriptions
as a loyalty program

00:15:46.290 --> 00:15:49.830
that provide premium access.

00:15:49.830 --> 00:15:53.520
Another thing to think about is
monthly versus yearly access.

00:15:53.520 --> 00:15:55.320
Right now, we just have monthly.

00:15:55.320 --> 00:15:57.810
And I'm going to tell you
a little story about why.

00:15:57.810 --> 00:16:00.510
So one of the unique things
about our culture at N3TWORK

00:16:00.510 --> 00:16:04.320
is that we believe great
ideas can come from anywhere.

00:16:04.320 --> 00:16:06.540
And our subscriptions
actually came

00:16:06.540 --> 00:16:09.300
from one of our client engineers
on legendary, [INAUDIBLE],,

00:16:09.300 --> 00:16:11.220
he came to us and
said, hey, Google's

00:16:11.220 --> 00:16:14.580
now offering the ability
to do subscriptions.

00:16:14.580 --> 00:16:16.470
I think we should
put that in our game,

00:16:16.470 --> 00:16:21.360
should be like the Amazon Prime
of subscriptions for Legendary.

00:16:21.360 --> 00:16:25.440
So we got a great feature
from our client engineer.

00:16:25.440 --> 00:16:28.110
But the downside was we
didn't have a 20 person design

00:16:28.110 --> 00:16:29.730
team thinking about it.

00:16:29.730 --> 00:16:32.970
So we didn't think of all the
ins and outs of subscriptions

00:16:32.970 --> 00:16:34.780
when we first implemented it.

00:16:34.780 --> 00:16:38.970
So we' got a really great
system but some constraints

00:16:38.970 --> 00:16:41.810
in that it's not as extensible
as we would like it to be.

00:16:41.810 --> 00:16:43.860
But we're fixing that now.

00:16:43.860 --> 00:16:46.200
Another thing to think
about is how much

00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:50.310
you can discount IAP for the
promise of future revenue.

00:16:50.310 --> 00:16:52.590
The bet we made was
that subscriptions

00:16:52.590 --> 00:16:54.450
would be highly retentive.

00:16:54.450 --> 00:16:58.950
So we bet long term future
revenue would benefit us.

00:16:58.950 --> 00:17:00.480
The other thing
to think about is

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:04.710
that subscriptions must provide
convenience to the player.

00:17:04.710 --> 00:17:07.220
You should make it a no brainer.

00:17:07.220 --> 00:17:10.349
A subscription player, after
having experienced playing

00:17:10.349 --> 00:17:14.940
the game with subscriptions,
cannot imagine playing the game

00:17:14.940 --> 00:17:17.730
ever again without
a subscription.

00:17:17.730 --> 00:17:19.230
The other thing you
need to consider

00:17:19.230 --> 00:17:23.160
is rewarding and celebrating
your loyal subscribers.

00:17:23.160 --> 00:17:29.100
Celebrate, celebrate, celebrate
through VIP events, VIP offers.

00:17:29.100 --> 00:17:31.590
Our VIPs can actually
reach us anytime

00:17:31.590 --> 00:17:33.720
of the day to give us feedback.

00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:36.630
Subscriber players
must feel like they

00:17:36.630 --> 00:17:40.470
belong to a community that's
appreciated by the game devs.

00:17:40.470 --> 00:17:43.845
And tie subscriptions to loyalty
programs whenever possible.

00:17:46.480 --> 00:17:48.230
So some challenges--
I'm going to talk

00:17:48.230 --> 00:17:51.830
about intuitive messaging
and stand out UX together

00:17:51.830 --> 00:17:54.230
because they kind
of go hand-in-hand.

00:17:54.230 --> 00:17:58.170
One thing we asked ourselves
was, how do we communicate

00:17:58.170 --> 00:18:01.430
VIP benefits in as
clear way as possible

00:18:01.430 --> 00:18:04.380
with as few words as possible?

00:18:04.380 --> 00:18:05.840
One of the ways
you can do that is

00:18:05.840 --> 00:18:09.530
by differentiating what the game
looks like for non-subscribers

00:18:09.530 --> 00:18:11.210
versus subscribers.

00:18:11.210 --> 00:18:13.400
One way we did this
was through color.

00:18:13.400 --> 00:18:17.060
Our non-subscribers, a steady
state of the game is blue.

00:18:17.060 --> 00:18:21.170
For our subscribers, it's
purple, the color of royalty.

00:18:21.170 --> 00:18:23.480
Everywhere you
get a VIP benefit,

00:18:23.480 --> 00:18:25.610
we theme it purple as
you can see from the mock

00:18:25.610 --> 00:18:27.080
up on the screen.

00:18:27.080 --> 00:18:28.820
If you turn off
the IAP, the game

00:18:28.820 --> 00:18:30.680
looks very different for you.

00:18:30.680 --> 00:18:32.150
It's pretty obvious.

00:18:32.150 --> 00:18:34.220
We built it into the core loop.

00:18:34.220 --> 00:18:38.420
If you play as a VIP, you can't
help but see the benefits.

00:18:38.420 --> 00:18:40.400
If you turn it
off, it's obvious.

00:18:40.400 --> 00:18:44.030
Everywhere you lost
something is super clear.

00:18:44.030 --> 00:18:45.680
We also think of
our VIPs as they're

00:18:45.680 --> 00:18:49.530
not only VIPs in the game
but also outside of the game.

00:18:49.530 --> 00:18:51.740
We actually have a Slack
channel where our VIPs

00:18:51.740 --> 00:18:53.590
can communicate with us.

00:18:53.590 --> 00:18:55.820
Their customer service
tickets get flagged,

00:18:55.820 --> 00:18:58.010
and they're handled separately.

00:18:58.010 --> 00:19:01.220
Every interaction
a subscriber player

00:19:01.220 --> 00:19:04.520
has must be a moment of
delight and reinforce

00:19:04.520 --> 00:19:07.280
that they are a VIP.

00:19:07.280 --> 00:19:11.270
Another thing to think about
is when to sell subscriptions.

00:19:11.270 --> 00:19:12.860
We run weekly events.

00:19:12.860 --> 00:19:16.340
So we might put a
pop-up in the game a day

00:19:16.340 --> 00:19:18.320
before an event
starts to advertise

00:19:18.320 --> 00:19:20.450
how what you get out
of a web subscription

00:19:20.450 --> 00:19:23.520
can help you in the events.

00:19:23.520 --> 00:19:26.210
This one I put in
here for the devs--

00:19:26.210 --> 00:19:29.150
shared account prevention.

00:19:29.150 --> 00:19:31.340
We needed to build
into a system a way

00:19:31.340 --> 00:19:34.430
to prevent multiple players
who share a single Google

00:19:34.430 --> 00:19:37.670
account from exploiting and
getting unfair advantages.

00:19:37.670 --> 00:19:42.290
And lastly, you need to ensure
that you have high caliber

00:19:42.290 --> 00:19:44.690
customer support and that
your customer support

00:19:44.690 --> 00:19:50.160
team is properly equipped
to benefit your subscribers.

00:19:50.160 --> 00:19:53.360
So IAP versus subscriptions--
many people think

00:19:53.360 --> 00:19:56.300
of subscriptions are
just auto-renewal of IAP.

00:19:56.300 --> 00:19:58.670
But we think of them
very differently.

00:19:58.670 --> 00:20:01.190
To echo what Moonlit
said earlier,

00:20:01.190 --> 00:20:03.530
subscriptions are access.

00:20:03.530 --> 00:20:07.520
They're highly retentive
long term access to content.

00:20:07.520 --> 00:20:08.780
IAP is content.

00:20:08.780 --> 00:20:12.350
It's a one time situational
purchase of content.

00:20:12.350 --> 00:20:15.620
Conceptually, we think
of them very differently.

00:20:15.620 --> 00:20:18.260
Subscriptions help
underwrite our revenue

00:20:18.260 --> 00:20:20.720
and improve our
pay or retention.

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:24.020
It also gives us a way to
personalize IAP offers based

00:20:24.020 --> 00:20:26.330
on a player's subscription
tier rather than having

00:20:26.330 --> 00:20:28.970
one store front for everyone.

00:20:28.970 --> 00:20:31.310
Subscriptions can
boost IAP economy

00:20:31.310 --> 00:20:34.430
through increased value of
products for subscribers.

00:20:34.430 --> 00:20:37.025
And this is at no cost
to other IAP products.

00:20:37.025 --> 00:20:40.910
So in other words, we have
seen no cannibalization.

00:20:40.910 --> 00:20:43.100
Some things we wish
we considered--

00:20:43.100 --> 00:20:45.320
Google's subscription
service has some really great

00:20:45.320 --> 00:20:46.490
features--

00:20:46.490 --> 00:20:50.240
free trials, auto-renewal
of trials and deals

00:20:50.240 --> 00:20:53.090
so, for instance, three
months at a discounted price,

00:20:53.090 --> 00:20:55.940
time cards, providing
an alternative IAP

00:20:55.940 --> 00:20:59.270
to gain temporary access to
subscribing so, for example,

00:20:59.270 --> 00:21:01.980
like a three month
Xbox Live card.

00:21:01.980 --> 00:21:05.680
Those are all things that
are currently on our roadmap.

00:21:05.680 --> 00:21:09.780
Now, if I'm going to leave
you with three key learnings,

00:21:09.780 --> 00:21:13.200
one would be, given
its high retention,

00:21:13.200 --> 00:21:17.460
VIP subscription should be the
number one thing people buy.

00:21:17.460 --> 00:21:19.380
It should be a no
brainer to them.

00:21:19.380 --> 00:21:22.260
The value they get out
of it is a no brainer.

00:21:22.260 --> 00:21:25.170
Two, framing is everything.

00:21:25.170 --> 00:21:28.800
Celebrate, celebrate,
celebrate your VIP subscribers

00:21:28.800 --> 00:21:31.710
both inside and
outside the game.

00:21:31.710 --> 00:21:35.490
And lastly, build fast
but maintain the ability

00:21:35.490 --> 00:21:36.540
to iterate.

00:21:36.540 --> 00:21:38.212
This is where we are now.

00:21:38.212 --> 00:21:39.420
Thanks so much for your time.

00:21:39.420 --> 00:21:41.387
And with that, I'll
give it back to Moonlit.

00:21:41.387 --> 00:21:43.375
[APPLAUSE]

00:21:43.375 --> 00:21:44.370
Thank you.

00:21:44.370 --> 00:21:46.160
MOONLIT BESHIMOV:
Thank you, Fay.

00:21:46.160 --> 00:21:49.220
Now let's conclude our session.

00:21:49.220 --> 00:21:51.770
As you think about the
takeaways for this session,

00:21:51.770 --> 00:21:54.330
I have three hopes for you.

00:21:54.330 --> 00:21:57.180
First, I hope you
found the inspiration

00:21:57.180 --> 00:22:01.000
to go back and reinvent
your monetization strategy.

00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:03.540
Second, I hope that
you believe now

00:22:03.540 --> 00:22:07.410
your past doesn't necessarily
dictate your future.

00:22:07.410 --> 00:22:09.990
And third, I hope you
will go back to your teams

00:22:09.990 --> 00:22:13.740
and ask them, why shouldn't
we diversify more?

00:22:13.740 --> 00:22:17.550
With this, I'll end the session
with one question for you.

00:22:17.550 --> 00:22:21.420
When was the last time you had a
sit down meeting with your team

00:22:21.420 --> 00:22:25.860
to actively decide the current
status quo is also the best

00:22:25.860 --> 00:22:28.360
strategy going forward?

00:22:28.360 --> 00:22:28.860
Thank you.

00:22:28.860 --> 00:22:30.710
[APPLAUSE]

